  "texts": [
    "For the right-to-left inclusion, by persistence for X, if x ∈ X, then for every minimal point a ⊑ x, a ∈ X, so h(x) ⊆ X, which implies h(x) ∈ X and hence x ∈ h -1 [X].",
    "Thus, h -1 [X] = X ∈ P. For robust, to show X = h -1 [h[X]], we show that if h(x) ∈ h[X], then x ∈ X.",
    "If h(x) ∈ h[X], then there is an x ′ ∈ X such that h(x) = h(x ′).From h(x) = h(x ′) we have that x ⊑ s x ′, which with x ′ ∈ X implies x ∈ X by Fact 4.2.",
    "Next, we must show that there is anX ∈ P ′℘ such that h[X] = h[S] ∩ X.",
    "Taking X = {Y ⊆ min⟨S, ⊑⟩ | ∅ ̸ = Y ⊆ X},we have X ∈ P ′℘ by the unpacking of definitions above."
